<subSubSection id="9AA9651CFFC7FFEBA1AA794E92CB09EB" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFC7FFEBA1AA794E92CB09EB" blockId="14.[163,779,532,922]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC7FFEBA1AA794E917C0858" box="[163,284,532,553]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Large adult-sized muscular 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC7FFEBA378794E936B085B" authorityName="PROSCH" authorityYear="1847" box="[625,779,532,554]" class="Cephalopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="14" pageNumber="1225" phylum="Mollusca" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Cranchioidea">Cranchioidea</taxonomicName>
with mantle locking apparatus having a modified (‘lazy’) ‘T’ shape; anal photophore in juveniles; buccal connectives attached to the ventral borders of ventral arms; nuchal-locking apparatus with two hook-like knobs on mantle component and opposing nuchal knobs and pits; tentacles with carpal locking apparatus; large and wide muscular rhomboidal fins inserted in the dorsolateral surface of the mantle; gladius with vanes projecting anteriorly; with multiple seminal receptacles in the buccal membrane; large, long, cylindrical, gelatinous egg masses; embryos and paralarvae covered by dense chromatophores.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
